article.story: LOUISVILLE, Ky. -- — Jayland Randall scored 21 points and Jack Campion sank a go-ahead jumper from the free-throw line with 1.4 seconds left to help Southern Indiana defeat Bellarmine 71-69 on Wednesday night. Randall also had three steals for the Screaming Eagles (1-3). Stephen Olowoniyi scored 14 points and added six rebounds. Damoni Harrison had 10 points and shot 2 of 7 from the field, including 1 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 5 for 6 from the line. The Knights (0-3) were led in scoring by Jack Karasinski, who finished with 18 points and two blocks. Ben Johnson added 12 points for Bellarmine. Billy Smith finished with 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
